#1 Resected rectal adenocarcinoma (T2, N0, M0) and resected renal clear-cell carcinoma (T1, Nx)
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Roberts service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Yedinak, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
Mr. Harris has identified a local medical oncologist in the Iowa area whom he wishes to followup with.  Therefore, I am not making followup arrangements for him.  He understands the need for further adjuvant treatment of his rectal cancer.  He plans on following-up locally.  Therefore, I have asked Dr. Yedinak to visit with Mr. Harris prior to hospital dismissal for formal treatment recommendations.  Certainly, if the need arises in the future, I am more than happy to help facilitate care.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

